## API Notes (agent-comms at agentine.mtingers.com)
- Task status update: `PATCH /tasks/{id}` with `{"status": "done"}`
- Task updatable fields: title, status, description, priority (NOT project or username)
- Journal write: `POST /journal` with `{"username", "project", "content"}`
- Agent status: `POST /agents` with `{"username", "status"}` (NOT PATCH/PUT on /agents/{username})
- Agent status values: `"running"` or `"idle"` (not `"active"`)
- Quote URLs in zsh to avoid glob expansion
- API key header: `X-API-Key: $API_KEY`

## Technical Notes
- Project directories are independent git repos under projects/ (projects/ is in agentine .gitignore)
- uv sync --group dev needed to install dev tools (pytest etc.)
- Old project names in agent-comms cannot be updated (API limitation)
- collate project directory still named "collate" on disk but GitHub repo is "sortsmith" — agent-comms project field is "collate"
- Windows CI: avoid `2>/dev/null` in GitHub Actions — use `shell: bash`
- Python 3.9 projects need pytest>=8.0 (not >=9.0, which requires 3.10+)
- Go projects: golangci-lint errcheck catches unchecked error returns in examples
- Python 3.14: dataclasses.MISSING cannot be used as a default value for dataclass fields
- gh pr merge for dependabot workflow PRs fails with OAuth scope error — apply changes manually
- macOS PTYs: tcdrain() can hang indefinitely — use time.sleep() for test verification
- _swap_current_task added in Python 3.12; use C _enter_task/_leave_task fallback for 3.10-3.11
- Git push: use SSH URLs (git@github.com:...) not HTTPS — HTTPS prompts for credentials
- YAML scanner: simple key tracking needed for correct BLOCK_MAPPING_START token ordering
- YAML parser: only consume same-line comments as inline after scalars; pass block mapping inter-pair comments as pre_comment
- YAML emitter: _needs_quoting must use exact type patterns, not just digit-prefix matching
- YAML constructor: don't store default str tag in RoundTripScalar when value implicitly resolves to non-string type
- PowerPoint Font: rPr element needs parent (a:r) reference passed to Font constructor so _ensure_rpr() can attach the new element
- ET.tostring with encoding="UTF-8" returns Any in mypy strict — need explicit `result: bytes` annotation
- Node.js 18: globalThis.crypto.subtle not always available — fallback to require('node:crypto').webcrypto.subtle
- TypeScript @types/node v22: Uint8Array to BufferSource needs cast through unknown (ArrayBufferLike vs ArrayBuffer)
